title: Watch Desiigner Deliver an Energetic A Cappella Freestyle
text:
Watch Desiigner Deliver an Energetic A Cappella Freestyle By Trace William Cowen happy to waste more of your time here: @tracecowen 
  Subscribe to Complex Video via Hot 97 Desiigner brought his signature out-of-this-world energy to Hot 97 Thursday, hitting Funkmaster Flex with an a cappella freestyle. "Everybody can't come up here," Flex reminded his audience as Desiigner prepared to deliver.
Image via YouTube The G.O.O.D. Music member then kicked his rapid-fire freestyle into overdrive by declaring his life "a game," and a game he's ready to play. For Flex, the freestyle warranted unbroken eye contact:

He also opened up about how he met his manager Zana Ray, his future plans, and much more:
Last week, Desiigner and Tyga released the snake-filled video for their collab "Gucci Snakes." The video has a lot of snakes in it. Did we mention the video has snakes? Seriously. This video has way too many fucking snakes in it:
Desiigner also recently dropped his new song "Outlet," a SoundsByCt, Vinylz, and Mike Dean-produced track which thus far has no visual affiliation with snakes. Peep it here.
